Larry,

  It would certainly be worth your time to take a look at the 9594/X.500
  Directory Services spec. from ISO/CCITT since a considerable amount of
  effort has gone into its development.  As Debbie states in her message
  the ISO Directory provides a general mechanism which can be applied to
  many naming structures but will suffer in performance for some specific
  environments.

  The ISO/CCITT Directory is designed to provide a "global" naming space
  for OSI networks that may or may not be connected.  It would be good to
  see the output of your task force consider how its name service will
  relate to and possibly interact with the ISO/CCITT Directory.

  - Chris

